              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>I am a mathematician and computer scientist. My <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-phd.xml" addr="dhsorens-phd" title="PhD in Formal Methods">PhD</fr:link> was in formal specification of smart contracts in Coq, focusing on the problem of ensuring that specifications actually reflect the high-level intentions of their designers. Formal proposition and proof catch my attention in computer science, from various angles. These days, I am mostly interested in <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-lean.xml" addr="dhsorens-lean" title="The Lean Theorem Prover">Lean</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Here you can see my <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-pubs.xml" addr="dhsorens-pubs" title="Peer-Reviewed Publications">publications</fr:link>, <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-talks.xml" addr="dhsorens-talks" title="Talks">talks</fr:link>, <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens-notes.xml" addr="dhsorens-notes" title="Notes">notes</fr:link>, and <fr:link type="local" href="dhsorens.xml" addr="dhsorens" title="Derek Sorensen">bio</fr:link>.</fr:p>
